Philadelphia - A couple's late-night argument near Drexel University in Philadelphia took a deadly turn when a random man intervened in their fight and fatally shot the boyfriend. Philadelphia police say the victim was pronounced dead late Tuesday night and that they have a man in custody. The shooting happened near one of the college's student housing complexes, but authorities wouldn't disclose if anyone involved are Drexel students. A police lieutenant says that the shooter didn't know the couple and that he shot the victim three times. An investigation is ongoing. Associated Press